revision.text:
'''Babar Kot''' is an archeological site belonging to [[Indus Valley Civilisation]] located in [[Saurashtra (region)|Saurashtra]] region of Gujarat State, India. It is {{nowrap|325 km}} away from [[Ahmedabad]] and {{nowrap|152 km}} away from [[Bhavnagar]] and located in [[Jafrabad|Jafarabad]] taluka.
==Excavation== [[Gregory Possehl]], of University of Pennsylvania has undertaken detailed study at this site as well as at [[Rojdi]] and [[Oriyo timbo]].
==Historical significance== This site is classified as belonging to Late Harappan period and measures about 2.7 hectares; Babar Kot had a stone fortification wall.<ref name=singh>{{cite book|last=Singh|first=Upinder|title=A History of Ancient and Early Medieval India : from the Stone Age to the 12th century|year=2008|publisher=Pearson Education|location=New Delhi|isbn=9788131711200|pages=222|url=https://books.google.com/?id=H3lUIIYxWkEC&pg=PA222&dq=babar+kot#v=onepage&q=babar%20kot&f=false}}</ref>
==Plant findings== Findings from this site include plant remains of millets, gram,<ref name=singh/> bajra(pennisetum typhoideum)etc.<ref name=history>{{cite book|last=Agnihotri|first=V.K.(Ed.)|title=Indian History|year=1981|publisher=Allied Publishers|location=Mumbai|pages=A–82|url=https://books.google.com/?id=MazdaWXQFuQC&pg=SL1-PA82&dq=babar+kot#v=onepage&q=babar%20kot&f=false|isbn=9788184245684}}</ref> Further, it is indicated that Bajra might be present at this site during third millennium BCE.<ref name=jane>{{cite book|last=McIntosh|first=Jane R.|title=The Ancient Indus Valley : New Perspectives|year=2008|publisher=ABC-CLIO|location=Santa Barbara, Calif.|isbn=9781576079072|pages=112|url=https://books.google.com/?id=1AJO2A-CbccC&printsec=frontcover&dq=mcintosh+jane#v=onepage&q=babar%20kot&f=false}}</ref> Babar kot provided evidence of two crops, one in summer and another during winter.<ref name=david>{{cite book|last=Nicholas David,|first=Carol Kramer|title=Ethnoarchaeology in Action|year=2001|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=New York|isbn=9780521667791|pages=132|url=https://books.google.com/?id=r__vIw_XUFEC&pg=PA132&dq=babar+kot#v=onepage&q=babar%20kot&f=false|edition=Digitally repr., with corr.}}</ref>
