'''''Bruckmann's Illustrated Guides''''' (1892-1916) were European travel [[guide book]]s published by A. Bruckmann in [[Munich]] and Asher & Co. in London.<ref>{{citation |title=Geographical Literature of the Month |work=Geographical Journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7bqRAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA395 |date=April 1895 |volume=5 }}</ref> The series also appeared in a German-language edition entitled ''Bruckmann's Illustrierte Reiseführer''.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Herzog August Bibliothek |location=[[Wolfenbüttel]], Germany |url= http://sunny.biblio.etc.tu-bs.de:8080/DB=2/LNG=EN/CLK?IKT=12&TRM=170784207 |work=Katalog |language=German |title=Bruckmanns illustrierte Reiseführer |accessdate=August 24, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=New Books |work=Scottish Geographical Magazine |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SoxIAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA550 |date=October 1895 |volume=11 }}</ref>

