{{unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Italic title}} '''''Cadernos Pagu''''' is a [[Brazil]]ian [[academic journal]] on [[gender studies]] and [[Human sexuality|sexuality]]. It was established in 1993 at the [[Universidade Estadual de Campinas]]. Pagu was the nickname of [[Patrícia Galvão]], an iconic Brazilian [[feminist]]. The journal is published in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and the [[editor-in-chief]] is Leila Mezan Algranti (Universidade Estadual de Campinas).
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in: * [[Sociological Abstracts]] * [[MLA International Bibliography]] * [[International Bibliography of Periodical Literature]] * [[International Bibliography of Book Reviews of Scholarly Literature]]
