'''''Intégral: The Journal of Applied Musical Thought''''' ({{ISSN|1073-6913}}) is a peer-reviewed, [[academic journal]] specializing in [[music theory]] and [[musical analysis|analysis]]. It began publication in 1987, under the auspices of graduate students in music theory at the [[Eastman School of Music]]. According to its website, "the journal pursues an implicit mandate to explore and exploit the increasing pluralism of the music-theoretic field."<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://theory.esm.rochester.edu/integral/ |title=''Intégral'' website. |access-date=2009-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090726110340/http://theory.esm.rochester.edu/integral/ |archive-date=2009-07-26 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
The journal's first editor was John Adrian. It is currently co-edited by Andrew Aziz and Samantha Inman.
