'''Rafael Navarro Núñez''' (April 25, 1946 – July 27, 2015) was a Spanish painter.

==Biography ==
Nuñez studied at ''la'' ''Escuela de Artes Aplicadas'' ''y Oficios Artísticos de [[Córdoba, Andalusia|Córdoba]]''  (the Córdoba School of Arts and Crafts), and in 1968 began advanced studies in the Santa Isabel of Hungary School of Fine Arts in [[Seville]]. In 1970, he joined the Saint Fernando School of Fine Arts of [[Madrid]], where he spent three years dedicated to painting, silkscreen printing, mural art, the xylography and chalcography. At the same time, he undertook four courses in Drawing in the ''Círculo de Bellas Artes'' in Madrid.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.eldiadecordoba.es/article/ocio/2079735/rafael/navarro/pintor/cordobes/la/voz/expresionista/muere/los/anos.html |title=Rafael Navarro, el pintor cordobés de la voz expresionista, muere |publisher=Eldiadecordoba.es |date=July 28, 2015 |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref>

From 1980 to 1986, Nuñez served as professor at the Córdoba School of Arts and Crafts, eventually leaving to devote himself entirely to painting.

He died in 2015.

== Career ==
[[File:Rafael Navarro, ante una de sus obras.jpg|280px|thumb|Rafael Navarro (2009)]]

His first individual exhibition was at the Madrilenian Gallery Novart in 1978. More than thirty individual exhibitions followed as well as other collective exhibitions.

Navarro liked to classify his work as [[expressionist]], somewhere between the Spanish "figuración" and [[abstract art|abstract]]. Madrid, where he spent ten years training, has always been a clear influence, especially in his grandmasters projects Goya (the [[Goya]] of the [[Black Paintings]]) as well as painters [[Francis Bacon (painter)|Francis Bacon]] and [[Antonio Saura]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariocordoba.com/noticias/cultura/fallece-pintor-expresionista-cordobes-rafael-navarro_977748.html |title=Fallece el pintor expresionista cordobés Rafael Navarro – Cultura – Diario Córdoba |publisher=Diariocordoba.com |date=July 28, 2015 |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref><ref name="arsoperandi1">{{cite web|url=http://www.arsoperandi.com/2015/07/muere-el-pintor-rafael-navarro.html |title=Fallece el pintor Rafael Navarro |publisher=Ars Operandi |date=July 27, 2015 |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref>

He participated in the collective sample, "60 Years of Contemporary Art", in Córdoba (1953–2013) which was celebrated in four headquarters at the same time in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.cordoba.es/uploads/Publicaciones/201412-60anios-catalogo.pdf |format=PDF |title=60 Anos De Arte Contemporaneo en Cordoba : 1953–2013 |publisher=Cultura.cordoba.es |accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref>

===Kassel exhibition===
In October 2012, he prepared a sample of his works, a magna exhibition with more than 130 works that covered more than 30 years of his work. Organized by Michael Wilkens, architect and chair of Theory of the Architecture of the [[University of Kassel]] and founder of the group Baufrösche (Ranitas constructors),<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.baufroesche.de/ |title=Baufrösche |publisher=Baufroesche.de |date= |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref> Navarro exhibited in the Atelier of Langestrasse ([[Kassel]], Germany) a group of works that were painted from 1980 to 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author=Manuel J. Albert |url=http://cordopolis.es/2012/10/01/rafael-navarro-el-lado-oscuro-de-la-condicion-humana/ |title=Navarro: el lado oscuro de la condición humana &#124; CORDÓPOLIS, el Diario Digital de Córdoba |publisher=Cordopolis.es |date= |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref> The exhibition displayed one of Navarro's last series, titled ''Nosferatu'', in addition to the series ''Matador'' and ''Toxic Landscape'', painted between 2004 and 2010. Eighteen pictures were added to the exhibition from the collector and commissioner of the exhibition, Alfonso Rodríguez, who contributed works between 1984 and 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariocordoba.com/noticias/cultura/rafael-navarro-expone-muestra-obra-alemania_754715.html |title=Rafael Navarro expone una muestra de su obra en Alemania – Cultura – Diario Córdoba |publisher=Diariocordoba.com |date=October 23, 2012 |accessdate=2015-09-05}}</ref>

