{{Infobox Museum |name = The Geological Museum and Art Gallery of Dilijan |native_name = Դիլիջանի երկրագիտական թանգարան-պատկերասրահ |native_name_lang = Armenian |image = Դիլիջանի երկրագիտական թանգարան 02.JPG |caption = |alt = |map_type = |map_caption = |map_alt = |latitude = |longitude = |established = 1950 (museum), 1958 (art gallery) |dissolved = |location = 28 Myasnikyan str. [[Dilijan]], [[Tavush Region]], [[Armenia]] |type = |collection = |visitors = |director = Ghazar Ghazaryan |president = |curator = |publictransit = |network = |website = }}
'''The Geological Museum and Art Gallery of Dilijan''' is a [[museum]] of [[local history]] and an [[art gallery]] in [[Dilijan]], [[Armenia]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Attraction_Review-g1160895-d6882916-Reviews-The_Geological_Museum_and_Art_Gallery_of_Dilijan-Dilijan_Tavush_Province.html | title=The Geological Museum and Art Gallery of Dilijan | website=[[TripAdvisor]] | accessdate=20 August 2016 }}</ref>
The museum was opened in 1950 by the teacher Yeghishe Hovsepyan. It provides a comprehensive view of the history of Dilijan, the historical development of the local people, their lifestile, culture monuments, historical and geographical conditions.<ref name="culturaldilijan">{{cite web|url=http://www.culturaldilijan.am/attract/gmag.html#.V7WtZNR94rh |title=Cultural Dilijan - Local History Museum and Art Gallery|publisher=culturaldilijan.am|accessdate=2016-08-18}}</ref> The art gallery was established in 1958.
==History== [[File:Շենք երկրագիտական թանգարանի, ArmAg (8).jpg|thumb]] Though the museum was established by Yeghishe Hovsepyan, its long-time director Albert Matinyan and the Honored Artist of the Republic of Armenia Hovhannes Sharambeyan made every effort to make it treasury of archaeological items and works of art.{{citation needed|date=August 2016}} Initially, all the items were collected in the town library. The former building of the museum was built in 1926 as a hotel, later used as a hospital and afterwards again was used as a hotel. It underwent reconstruction in 1927 to host the Geological Museum and Art Gallery of Dilijan. The old building of the museum was demolished, and during five years new building of the museum was built. The official opening of the museum was held in 2010. It was opened to the public on 1 April 2011.{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}
==Collections== [[File:Շենք երկրագիտական թանգարանի, ArmAg (10).jpg|thumb]] The museum exhibits the original works of [[Hovhannes Aivazovsky]], [[Gevorg Bashinjaghian]], [[Vardges Sureniants]], [[Panos Terlemezyan]], [[Edgar Chahine]], [[Lev Lagorio]], and [[Jean-Baptiste Greuzeare]].{{citation needed|date=August 2016}} It has also works of Dutch, Italian and French painters of the 16th, 17th, and 18th centuries, as well as paintings by the American painter [[Rockwell Kent]] and works of [[Jean Carzou]].
