'''Wolfgang Schweickard''' (born 16 October 1954 in [[Aschaffenburg]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[Romance studies]] scholar and [[lexicographer]].
His main research areas are history of Romance languages and lexicography. He is co-editor of the ''[[Zeitschrift für romanische Philologie]]'' and the yearbook ''Lexicographica''. Current projects are the ''[[Deonomasticon Italicum]]'' (DI), the ''[[Lessico etimologico italiano]] (LEI)'' (together with [[Max Pfister]]) and the ''[[Dictionnaire étymologique des langues romanes]]'' (DÉRom) (together with [[Eva Buchi]]).
